cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "chokepoint-research-engine: A pre-registered, agent-assisted framework for thematic investment research"
message: "If you use this framework, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Zheng
    given-names: Yixing
repository-code: "https://github.com/yixingz3/chokepoint-research-engine"
abstract: >-
  A domain-agnostic framework for using LLM agents to conduct disciplined thematic
  investment research. It wraps open-ended agentic discovery in deterministic gates
  and a forward pre-registration ("forward-QPOP") protocol to resist confabulation,
  narrative drift, over-admission, and backtest overfitting. Contributions include a
  portable bottleneck graph, a decomposed confidence model, a budget-aware
  cheap-source / deterministic-gate / expensive-evaluate funnel, and forward
  validation via paper trading and conservative shadow fills.
keywords:
  - large language models
  - agentic research
  - pre-registration
  - investment research
  - supply-chain bottlenecks
  - trustworthy AI in finance
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0
date-released: "2026-06-07"
